{
  "stem": "2804.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to be careful of booby traps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, one of the rooms, they found a box-- and I'll never forget this-- with eggs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there were empty egg shells.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And attached to the top was like a little electrical device.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, how they got the yolk out and the tiny little hole, there were no-- and so one of the soldiers, one of the GIs, just picked it up and threw it out the window.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a-- one of the booby traps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the-- they scanned the rooms pretty well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we brought in our own cots and-- and-- and our own equipment that we stayed there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we had a meeting with our colonel and with everybody and the doctors.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, we had to start somewhere, and decide, well, the best thing to do, we had to clean out the barracks, the German barracks, because then we thought that the-- then we knew that the-- that the army would send in like double-decker beds for us.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Were there any Germans alive when you arrived in this camp?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they-- as I said, they were the ones that were being-- not that we-- that we spoke to personally, no.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- these would-- and they-- these were people, you have no idea the skeletons, actually skeletons, how they could walk around.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were people from all over Europe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember taking a couple people out of the compound.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We would put them on cots to take them into the barracks there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember so vividly a famous-- he was a famous musician-- I don't remember his name-- at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- that he was there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And what we tried to do is to give plasma to these people.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
